# TASK_PACKET

Task ID
CRUSHR-FORMAT-13

Title
Evaluate dictionary-encoded path identity with deterministic mirror placement

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Implement and compare dictionary-encoded path identity variants that replace repeated inline path strings with compact path references plus deterministically placed dictionary copies, then measure whether they preserve FORMAT-12 named recovery while materially reducing stress-case size overhead.

This packet exists because:

- FORMAT-12 proved that `extent_identity_inline_path` restores named recovery at far lower cost than manifest-heavy designs
- FORMAT-12-STRESS proved that inline naming remains viable, but repeated path strings still impose measurable per-extent cost
- the next bounded hypothesis is that a compact path dictionary plus deterministic mirror placement can preserve the recovery benefit while reducing size overhead further

This packet is an evidence packet, not a final canonical lock unless results are overwhelmingly clear.

