Context

Current result state:

- `extent_identity_only` is now a legacy research variant
- `extent_identity_inline_path` is the leading identity-layer candidate
- manifest-bearing variants are structurally inferior on size
- remaining inefficiency comes from repeating full path strings in every extent identity record

FORMAT-12-STRESS showed:
- named recovery parity remained intact under adversarial path/fragmentation pressure
- inline path duplication still cost ~142 bytes per extent in the stress corpus
- inline path remained far smaller than manifest-bearing designs, but there is a plausible further optimization

This packet tests whether compact path references plus small mirrored dictionaries can preserve the same recovery behavior at lower byte cost.

